  "prompt": "Which is the best sports bra?",
  "response": "The \"best\" sports bra depends on your specific needs, including the type of physical activity, your body size, and personal comfort preferences. Here are some highly rated sports bras across different categories to help you decide:\n\n### **High-Support Sports Bras (for high-impact activities like running, HIIT, etc.)**\n1. **Brooks Dare Crossback Run Bra**  \n   - Great for high-impact activities.  \n   - Wide, adjustable straps for comfort.  \n   - Moisture-wicking fabric.  \n\n2. **Nike Alpha Ultrabreathe**  \n   - Lightweight and breathable.  \n   - High support for intense workouts.  \n   - Stylish design.  \n\n3. **Lululemon Energy Bra High Support**  \n   - Versatile support for medium to high-impact activities.  \n   - Seamless fabric for comfort.  \n\n### **Medium-Support Sports Bras (for yoga, pilates, or light workouts)**\n1. **Athleta Conscious Elite Bra**  \n   - Eco-friendly fabric.  \n   - Medium support with a sleek design.  \n\n2. **Under Armour Infinity Mid Sports Bra**  \n   - Comfortable for medium-impact activities.  \n   - Soft, stretchy fabric.  \n\n3. **Adidas Cloudfoam Pure Sports Bra**  \n   - Lightweight and comfortable.  \n   - Ideal for everyday wear or light workouts.  \n\n### **Low-Support Sports Bras (for lounging, walking, or low-impact activities)**\n1. **Beyond Yoga Spacedye Unwind Bra**  \n   - Ultra-soft and comfortable.  \n   - Perfect for lounging or light yoga.  \n\n2. **Calvin Klein Performance Cotton Sports Bra**  \n   - Simple and supportive for low-impact activities.  \n   - Classic design.  \n\n### **Tips for Choosing the Best Sports Bra**\n- **Support Level:** Match the bra to your activity (low, medium, or high impact).  \n- **Fit:** Ensure it\u2019s snug but not too tight; you should be able to breathe comfortably.  \n- **Material:** Look for moisture-wicking, breathable fabrics.  \n- **Adjustability:** Adjustable straps and closures can help achieve the perfect fit.  \n\nUltimately, the best sports bra is one that provides the support you need, feels comfortable, and fits well. It\u2019s often worth trying on a few different brands and styles to find your perfect match!",
